label: rubber cement
definition: Masonry cement which comprises a mixture of elastic polymers mixed in a solvent.
editors note: Solvents typically used include acetone, hexane, heptane or toluene.

label: wallpaper paste
definition: An adhesive material which is used to fix wallpaper to walls.

label: permanent hair dye
definition: A coloring agent which is used to permanently alter hair color.

label: pharmaceutical ink
definition: An water-based ink which is ingestible and used to print onto pill medications.

label: gel ink
definition: An ink which is high viscosity and opaque, and used in gel pens.

label: soy ink
definition: An slow drying ink which is made from refined soybean oil.

label: aqueous inkjet printer ink
definition: A coloring agent which is used to deposit color onto a substrate via an inkjet printer.

label: emissions from gasoline combustion
definition: A mixture of gases and particles which is produced from the combustion of petroleum fuels in vehicles.

label: ink
definition: A manufactured product which contains a colourant that used to imprint upon materials.
